  <title>Cogl.Pipeline.prototype.set_layer_point_sprite_coords_enabled</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_layer_point_sprite_coords_enabled(layer_index: Number(gint), enable: <link xref="Cogl.Bool">Cogl.Bool</link>): <link xref="Cogl.Bool">Cogl.Bool</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_pipeline_set_layer_point_sprite_coords_enabled()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>When rendering points, if <code>enable</code> is <code>true</code> then the texture
coordinates for this layer will be replaced with coordinates that
vary from 0.0 to 1.0 across the primitive. The top left of the
point will have the coordinates 0.0,0.0 and the bottom right will
have 1.0,1.0. If <code>enable</code> is <code>false</code> then the coordinates will be
fixed for the entire point.</p>  <p>This function will only work if <link xref="Cogl.FeatureID"/>.ogl_feature_id_point_sprite is
available. If the feature is not available then the function will
return <code>false</code> and set @error.</p>
  <p>Since 2.0</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>layer_index</code></title>
  <p>the layer number to change.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>enable</code></title>
  <p>whether to enable point sprite coord generation.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p><code>true</code> if the function succeeds, <code>false</code> otherwise.</p>
</item>
